  <prompt>
    Extend `PlaybookExecutionEngine.ExecuteChatSummarizeAsync` (Path 3) to invoke `JpsRefResolver.ResolveAsync` BEFORE the streaming LLM call, per spec FR-38 + design §WP6 recommendation (b). The canonical Path 1 invocation lives at `AiAnalysisNodeExecutor.cs:442-499` — replicate the pattern. Streaming behavior MUST remain unchanged per ADR-033: `StreamStructuredCompletionAsync` + `IncrementalJsonParser` + `FieldDelta` SSE-event emission per top-level field stays intact. `$ref` resolution happens in prompt assembly only, before any streaming.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE BFF AI engineer. Expert in Path 1/2/3 execution model + streaming Structured Outputs.</role>

  <goal>
    `PlaybookExecutionEngine.ExecuteChatSummarizeAsync` calls `JpsRefResolver.ResolveAsync` before the streaming LLM call when the action's systemPrompt contains JPS `$ref` markers. Resolved prompt (Skill PromptFragments + Knowledge Content inlined) is passed to `StreamStructuredCompletionAsync`. Streaming hot path (per-field SSE emission) unchanged. Unit test confirms resolver invoked when refs present; integration test confirms streaming behavior identical.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec FR-38 + design §WP6 (b) Recommendation. Path 3 (`PlaybookExecutionEngine.ExecuteChatSummarizeAsync` at line ~185) currently bypasses Skill/Knowledge composition — it goes directly from action.SystemPrompt to streaming LLM call. Specialized playbooks (Summarize-NDA, Summarize-Patent, Extract-Invoice) need JPS `$ref` composition; without this engine change, they cannot reuse seeded Skills + Knowledge primitives. Q7 resolved: streaming MUST be preserved; resolution happens BEFORE LLM call.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PlaybookExecutionEngine.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Nodes/AiAnalysisNodeExecutor.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/JpsRefResolver.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Scopes/IScopeResolverService.cs</file>
      <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-033">Streaming chat tool side-channel preservation — `FieldDelta` SSE events per top-level field MUST emit unchanged; `IncrementalJsonParser` flow untouched; resolution happens BEFORE LLM call only.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Stay within `Services/Ai/` boundary; do not leak `IOpenAiClient` / `IPlaybookService` into CRUD code.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-014">If `JpsRefResolver` makes Dataverse lookups, those calls hit the 5-min ADR-014 cache layer in `IScopeResolverService` — verify cache key still tenant-scoped.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Per-task BFF publish-size measurement required — expect minor delta only (engine wiring + DI is small).</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-38 acceptance — unit test verifies `JpsRefResolver.ResolveAsync` called; streaming integration test continues to emit `FieldDelta` per top-level field.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Per CLAUDE.md §10 — test update obligation: PRs modifying `Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/` MUST update `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/`.</constraint>
  </constraints>

